Day 10 - Alternative Bug Tracking Tools & Test Management
Objective

To explore alternative bug tracking tools and learn test management by organizing test artifacts, creating test cases in TestRail, executing test runs, linking defects, and preparing test execution reports.

Tools Used
TestRail (Free Trial)
Google Sheets / Excel
GitHub
Tools Covered (Alternative Bug Tracking Tools)

Studied and compared popular bug tracking and test management tools such as:

Bugzilla
MantisBT
JIRA
TestRail
Zephyr
qTest
Activities Performed
Created tools comparison matrix based on features, pricing, reporting, and usability
Designed test management workflow (Requirement → Test Cases → Execution → Defects → Reports)
Set up TestRail project and created test suite structure
Added module-wise sections (Login, Registration, Cart, Checkout, Payment)
Added test cases with steps and expected results
Created a test run (Sprint 1 Execution) and updated results (Pass/Fail/Blocked/Retest)
Linked failed test cases with defect IDs for traceability
Prepared execution reports and dashboards:
Daily Test Status Report
Weekly Test Summary Report
Test Execution Dashboard
Defect Summary Report
Metrics Dashboard
Deliverables Completed
Tools Comparison Matrix
TestRail Setup (Suite, Sections, Test Cases, Test Run)
Test Execution Tracking Reports
Defect Summary Report
Metrics Dashboard
Conclusion

Day 10 helped in understanding different bug tracking tools and gaining practical experience in test management, execution tracking, defect traceability, and reporting using TestRail.
Day 10 helped in learning how QA teams manage test cases, execute test runs, track defects, and generate reports using TestRail and spreadsheets.
